<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">As late as 1946, the <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Sussex_Daily_News&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Sussex Daily News (page does not exist)">Sussex Daily News</a></i> stated that "Everybody connected with its administration is utterly opposed to Hove being the satellite of any other borough. It is willing to be enlarged but not to be absorbed.<sup id="cite_ref-EncH&amp;Pv1p69_6-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EncH&amp;Pv1p69-6">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
